oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real photo postcard of soldier in overcoat
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This picture postcard of soldier in overcoat with pistol belt and two clip puches for Colt .45 automatic pistol is part of the American Third Army during the occupaton of the Rhineland from 1919-1923. He is wearing his service cap and puttees.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
